itemDescription: British Conservative politician and Governor of New Zealand (1853–1911)

wikipedia_page.main: William Hillier Onslow, 4th Earl of Onslow  (7 March 1853 – 23 October 1911) was a British Conservative politician. He held several governmental positions between 1880 and 1905 and was also Governor of New Zealand between 1889 and 1892.
